<section id="cloud-agents" class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-accent">
      A related question
    </p>
    <h2
      class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
    >
      Meta-harnesses and cloud agents
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
      <p>
        Cloud agents address some of these concerns, but in a different way.
        Environment snapshots deliver durability by freezing the whole machine
        rather than preserving the session as a first-class object. Cloud agents
        also offer their own collaboration affordances. So they solve some of
        the same problems from a different angle.
      </p>
      <p>
        Meta-harnesses aren't about where things run. They're about the extra
        affordances layered on top. You can run a meta-harness over local
        harnesses or over cloud agents; <mark>the point is what sits above them,
        not where the compute lives</mark>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
